<item>
  <title>Are legal expenses for litigation necessitated by changes to the election due to  coronavirus eligible CARES expenses?</title>
  <link>https://www.eac.gov/faq/are-legal-expenses-litigation-necessitated-changes-election-due-coronavirus-eligible-cares-1</link>
  <description><![CDATA[
<span class="taxonomyterm20176feed">Are legal expenses for litigation necessitated by changes to the election due to  coronavirus eligible CARES expenses?</span>


  
    <h5>Question</h5>
                  Are legal expenses for litigation necessitated by changes to the election due to coronavirus eligible CARES expenses?
              

<span class="taxonomyterm20176feed"><a title="View user profile." href="https://www.eac.gov/user/1906" lang about="https://www.eac.gov/user/1906" typeof="Person" property="schema:name" datatype class="taxonomyterm20176feed">shirschfield</a></span>

<span class="taxonomyterm20176feed">Monday, November 14, 2022
</span>


  
    <h5>Answer</h5>
                  <p>HAVA, in Section 101(b)(2), specifically states that 101 funds cannot be used to pay costs associated with any litigation, except to the extent that such costs otherwise constitute permitted uses of a payment under this section. Therefore, they cannot be used to cover the costs of a lawsuit brought against an action the state takes such as moving a primary or changing voting processes. However, if the litigation pertained to a state's actions to mitigate the effects of the pandemic on federal elections and the litigation resulted in a judgement or order requiring the state to implement certain changes in their administration of those elections, the funds could be used to carry out those required changes</p>
              


  
    <h5>FAQ Tags</h5>
        
                    <a href="https://www.eac.gov/taxonomy/term/20126" hreflang="en">Compliance</a>
              <a href="https://www.eac.gov/taxonomy/term/20026" hreflang="en">Federal Elections</a>
              <a href="https://www.eac.gov/taxonomy/term/20176" hreflang="en">HAVA</a>
                
      
<span class="a2a_kit a2a_kit_size_30 addtoany_list" data-a2a-url="https://www.eac.gov/faq/are-legal-expenses-litigation-necessitated-changes-election-due-coronavirus-eligible-cares-1" data-a2a-title="Are legal expenses for litigation necessitated by changes to the election due to  coronavirus eligible CARES expenses?"><a class="a2a_dd addtoany_share" href="https://www.addtoany.com/share#url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eac.gov%2Ffaq%2Fare-legal-expenses-litigation-necessitated-changes-election-due-coronavirus-eligible-cares-1&amp;title=Are%20legal%20expenses%20for%20litigation%20necessitated%20by%20changes%20to%20the%20election%20due%20to%20%20coronavirus%20eligible%20CARES%20expenses%3F"></a></span>
